            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your<strong> parsley</strong> roughly, including the stalks</p><p>Return the <strong>drained</strong> <strong>potatoes</strong> to a low heat with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a splash of <strong>milk</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped parsley </strong>and the juice of <strong>half</strong> your<strong> lemon[s] </strong>and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and mash until smooth – this is your<strong> lemony parsley mash</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>blanched peas</strong> to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over them to refresh them</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
